Johannesburg – The non-profit organistion, the Class of 76 Foundation (CO76F), is campaigning for free education in South Africa. CO76F wants to propose a free education campaign along with an education levy. CO76F is a non-profit Organisation established in honour of students who sparked the revolution in 1976 The main objectives are: The current project is the implementation of free education. <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-72230" src="http://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/4738868A-2F58-480B-9FD5-63883D77C61B-403x800.jpeg" alt="" width="403" height="800" srcset="https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/4738868A-2F58-480B-9FD5-63883D77C61B-403x800.jpeg 403w, https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/4738868A-2F58-480B-9FD5-63883D77C61B-126x250.jpeg 126w, https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/4738868A-2F58-480B-9FD5-63883D77C61B-211x420.jpeg 211w, https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/4738868A-2F58-480B-9FD5-63883D77C61B.jpeg 644w" sizes="(max-width: 403px) 100vw, 403px" /> “CO76F hereby invites like-minded organisations to join it in lobbying Parliament to legislate the introduction of the Education Levy (EG 5%) on all goods sold in SA, to assist government in providing free education,” CO76F said in a statement. Follow Class of 76 Foundation on Twitter by clicking here. The main objective is to: <img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-72181" src="http://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Free-education-713x800.jpg" alt="" width="696" height="781" srcset="https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Free-education-713x800.jpg 713w, https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Free-education-223x250.jpg 223w, https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Free-education-696x781.jpg 696w, https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Free-education-375x420.jpg 375w, https://sundayworld.co.za/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Free-education.jpg 749w" sizes="